1
00:00:04,078 --> 00:00:10,544
We’re interested in 
the Absolute Truth.

2
00:00:12,084 --> 00:00:16,442
There’s Absolute Truth 
and relative truth.

3
00:00:16,844 --> 00:00:19,564
[Golden Mean of the Infinite]

4
00:00:19,841 --> 00:00:24,980
Śrila Guru Mahārāj
tells us the word ‘sādhu’

5
00:00:24,985 --> 00:00:30,236
is based upon the word ‘sat’,
which means ‘eternal’.

6
00:00:30,236 --> 00:00:36,294
The sādhus, they’re interested 
in the eternal world, the permanent world.

7
00:00:37,008 --> 00:00:41,849
Vadanti tat tattva-vidas
tattvaḿ yaj jñānam advayam

8
00:00:41,849 --> 00:00:45,599
brahmeti paramātmeti
bhagavān iti śabdyate 
[SB: 1.2.11].

9
00:00:46,599 --> 00:00:50,779
This advaya-jnan,
this one thing to be known,

10
00:00:50,779 --> 00:00:53,272
can be understood in terms
of three aspects:

11
00:00:53,272 --> 00:00:56,659
Brahmā, Paramātmā 
and Bhagavān.

12
00:00:57,444 --> 00:01:00,846
Brahman, impersonal conceptions,

13
00:01:00,846 --> 00:01:05,989
appear superficially
to be able to contain everything.

14
00:01:06,944 --> 00:01:14,729
Paramātmā, at the other extreme,
smaller than the smallest.

15
00:01:14,859 --> 00:01:21,187
So, Guru Mahārāj 
poses the question in this way,

16
00:01:21,732 --> 00:01:25,677
“If these are the extremes 
of the Infinite,

17
00:01:25,677 --> 00:01:32,136
and in reference to this question,
the extremes of the Absolute,

18
00:01:32,794 --> 00:01:36,622
what will be 
the central conception?

19
00:01:36,622 --> 00:01:40,510
What is the central conception
of the Infinite?”

20
00:01:40,510 --> 00:01:45,735
kṛṣṇera yateka khelā, sarvottama nara-līlā,
nara-vapu tāhāra svarūpa
 

21
00:01:45,735 --> 00:01:52,077
gopa-veśa, veṇu-kara, nava-kiśora, naṭa-vara,
nara-līlāra haya anurūpa 
[Cc: 2.21.101]

22
00:01:52,396 --> 00:02:00,096
The central conception of the Infinite,
means ‘the golden mean’,

23
00:02:00,096 --> 00:02:03,220
 
is Kṛṣṇa conception,

24
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:05,014
which is distinguished by what?

25
00:02:05,014 --> 00:02:08,219
Human-like proportions.

26
00:02:08,219 --> 00:02:11,108
So it’s easier for people 
to accommodate

27
00:02:11,108 --> 00:02:14,971
the Infinite as being greater
than the greatest

28
00:02:14,971 --> 00:02:17,023
that they can think of,

29
00:02:17,023 --> 00:02:19,761
or even smaller 
than the smallest.

30
00:02:19,761 --> 00:02:22,694
But to think of the Infinite,

31
00:02:22,694 --> 00:02:24,990
the central conception 
of the Infinite,

32
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:29,677
the aprākṛta-līlā of Kṛṣṇa
which is a-prākṛta—

33
00:02:29,677 --> 00:02:33,338
like mundane, but not.

34
00:02:33,338 --> 00:02:34,515
Human-like.

35
00:02:34,515 --> 00:02:36,854
Human-like dimensions,
human-like proportions.

36
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:39,068
So it’s that
Supreme Absolute Truth

37
00:02:39,068 --> 00:02:41,603
Brahmā, Paramātmā,
and Bhagavān.

38
00:02:41,603 --> 00:02:43,957
But even within Bhagavān
there’s gradation.

39
00:02:43,957 --> 00:02:49,953
From Lakṣmī–Narāyaṇ, Sītā–Rām,
Rukmiṇī–Dvārkadhiś,

40
00:02:49,953 --> 00:02:54,772
and Radhā–Kṛṣṇa and
the Vraja-gopis in Vrīndāvan.

41
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:59,499
Whenever we speak 
of these things,

42
00:02:59,499 --> 00:03:04,576
there are many levels that 
they’re to be understood on,

43
00:03:04,603 --> 00:03:11,939
and it’s like
the spiritual version

44
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:14,412
of the unified fields theory,

45
00:03:14,412 --> 00:03:18,604
that proper siddhānta 
will help us

46
00:03:18,604 --> 00:03:22,304
understand everything
in it’s proper place.

47
00:03:22,304 --> 00:03:26,398
But even in the Supreme Absolute Truth
there’s gradation.

48
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:29,191
Yes, that is good, 
but go further.

49
00:03:29,191 --> 00:03:30,926
Can you go further?

50
00:03:30,926 --> 00:03:33,875
Guru Mahārāj’s 
paraphrase of this is

51
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:36,847
“Dive deep into Reality”.

